The Association of Advertising Agencies (AAAN), an umbrella body of the advertising companies operating in Nigeria, is set to hold its 49th annual general meeting and congress (AGM). The 49th AGM, themed ‘The new world order: technology as a game changer’, will hold in Lagos on July 22, 2022. In a statement on Sunday, AAAN said Babajide Sanwo-Olu, governor of Lagos state, and Lai Mohammed, minister of information and culture are among the dignitaries expected to attend the congress. It added that Sanwo-Olu will be declaring the AGM open while Lai Mohammed, whose ministry oversees advertising, will grace the event as the keynote speaker as well as the special guest of honour. Other expected speakers at the event include; David Okeme, executive director, System Specs; Olu Akanmu, president and co-chief executive officer, Opay Nigeria; Adetayo Bamiduro chief executive officer and co-founder Max.Ng; Niyi Yusuf, managing partner, Verraki Africa; and Juliet Ehimuan-Chiazor, Google country manager. The following panelists are also expected to grace the occasion; Norden Thurston, marketing director, Seven Up; Kelechi Nwosu, managing director, TBWA; Jay Chukwuemeka, partner, Imaginarium; and Ose Osundeko chief operating officer, Digitas Nigeria.